  "reading": "Canonical UF_CAT eps_0 = 22.90 +/- 0.78% reproduces the prior F011 result exactly (sanity check passed at pooled 46.39%). The Option 3 conductor-shuffle null is the most informative test: under real conductor, eps_0 = 22.90%; under 50 shuffled-conductor permutations, all fits hit the -50% lower bound (shuf_std=0.000). The fit has NO degenerate 'finds eps_0 regardless of data' mode \u2014 real conductor produces real decay. Option 2 (UF_SIMPLE eps_0=-46.94%, UF_MEANCOND eps_0=100.00%) gives different answers, BUT these alternatives do not map onto the GUE=0.178 theoretical baseline that defines the deficit. UF_SIMPLE uses only the leading-order density so the variance-to-GUE comparison isn't valid; UF_MEANCOND applies a single N globally and the fit fails to converge (chi2=10881). Apples-to-apples comparison would require re-deriving the theoretical GUE benchmark under each alternative unfolding, which requires analytic work beyond this audit. Verdict: F011 rank-0 residual SURVIVES the tractable checks \u2014 not a fitting artifact of the canonical unfolding. The eps_0 = 22.90 +/- 0.78 % claim under EPS011@v1 conventions holds.",
